"version": "1.0.4",
"title": "1512: Trinity, equality of the persons",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1512",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The Son and the Holy Spirit are equal to God the Father in eternity, nature and status. Within the Trinity the Father is head, first among equals; the Son and the Holy Spirit do the Father's will, glorifying him and making him known; and the Holy Spirit glorifies and makes known the Son.</p>\n<h2>The Son is equal with the Father</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:18\">JHN 5:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:23\">JHN 5:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:16\">JHN 8:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:9\">JHN 14:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:10\">JHN 17:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6\">PHP 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:9\">COL 2:9</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:7\">ROM 1:7</a></strong> <em>The equality of the Son and the Father is often implied in the opening greetings of the NT letters.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:3\">1CO 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:3\">GAL 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:2\">EPH 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:1\">1TH 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:2\">1TI 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:3\">PHM 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:2\">2PE 1:2</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:13\">REV 5:13</a></strong> <em>Doxologies are addressed to the Father and the Son equally or just to the Son.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:5\">ROM 9:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:21\">HEB 13:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:18\">2PE 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:10\">REV 7:10</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit is equal with the Father and the Son</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:14\">2CO 13:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19\">MAT 28:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:4-Rev1:5\">REV 1:4–1:5</a></p>\n<h2>The obedience of the Son to the Father</h2>\n<h3>The Son submits to the Father in his incarnation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6-Phil2:7\">PHP 2:6–2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:36\">MAT 24:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:34\">JHN 4:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:38\">JHN 6:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:28\">JHN 14:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:31\">JHN 14:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:19\">ROM 5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:8\">HEB 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:5-Heb10:7\">HEB 10:5–10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:6-Ps40:8\">PSA 40:6–40:8</a></p>\n<h3>The Father is Jesus Christ's ``head''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:3\">1CO 11:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:23\">1CO 3:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:6\">1CO 8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:27-1Cor15:28\">1CO 15:27–15:28</a></p>\n<h2>Equality and mutuality as the three persons glorify one another</h2>\n<h3>The Son glorifies the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:27\">ROM 16:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:13\">JHN 14:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:5-Eph1:6\">EPH 1:5–1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:21\">EPH 3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:11\">PHP 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:17\">COL 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:11\">1PE 4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:25\">JUD 1:25</a></p>\n<h3>The Father and the Son glorify one another</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:1\">JHN 17:1</a></strong> <em>In John's Gospel, the “glory” of Jesus Christ is seen above all in the cross.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:54\">JHN 8:54</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:31-John13:32\">JHN 13:31–13:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:4-John17:5\">JHN 17:4–17:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:24\">JHN 17:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:13\">ACT 3:13</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit glorifies the Father and the Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:13-John16:15\">JHN 16:13–16:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:26\">JHN 14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26\">JHN 15:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13-Eph1:14\">EPH 1:13–1:14</a></p>",
